So I'm just going to go ahead and knit this file, because there is one thing that I want

00:46:22.979 --> 00:46:24.179
to show you all.

00:46:24.179 --> 00:46:35.860
It's not specific to an R Markdown Shiny app, but hopefully you'll find it helpful.

00:46:35.860 --> 00:46:43.820
So this app is a little bit more analytically, I would say, well, at least time-consuming

00:46:43.820 --> 00:46:44.979
than the other one, right?

00:46:44.979 --> 00:46:50.060
It's building a portfolio, calculating standard deviations, and then the contributions over

